id: pm-l40h
title: MCP tools/call structuredContent.result is always present but isError path lacks it — inconsistent envelope
description: "On success, resultContent() returns `{ content: [...], structuredContent: { result, warnings? } }`. On error (errorContent()), it returns `{ isError: true, content: [...], structuredContent: { error, code } }`. The two envelopes are structurally different: success uses `structuredContent.result`, error uses `structuredContent.error`. MCP 2025-06-18 spec does not mandate a unified envelope, but clients that parse structuredContent generically must branch. A consistent shape would be `structuredContent: { ok: boolean, result?: ..., error?: string, code?: number, warnings?: string[] }` which allows typed SDK consumers to handle both cases uniformly."
type: Issue
status: open
priority: 3
